I think the chain of events is good for the world.  Anyone that lives some pipedream of some &quot;New World Order&quot; or single nationalism needs to put the pipe down and look at human history for the past 5000 years.  France/Germany already gave proof as evidence of why such a Utopian concept can never exist... rivalry and a thirst for power.  The sad thing is how Turkey is the recent victim caught in this &quot;West vs. France/EU&quot; struggle and in the end it's going to be lose-lose no matter what they do.  Where there is a leader, there will always be 100's trying to dismount and claim the throne as their own.  It's a fact of life.  What dictates morality and ethic is to what extent they will go to in order to claim such crown.   <br>
<br>
In conclusion, America isn't concerned what a bunch of rag heads that are being spoon fed state-financed propaganda and media think.  If you read about the latest protests and terrorists volunteering to enter Iraq and fight, most every one of them references &quot;children with no heads&quot; and similar.  They have been spoon fed the idealism that marines are running around with machetes and decapitating Iraqi civilians by the 1000's and therefore are going to go their duty and defend the Iraqi's against this aggression.  I can't say I blame them.  If I were being bombarded with solely reports of Marines butchering, torturing, killing, raping and kidnapping Iraqi citizens, all the while Sadamm has been striving to curb the incline of famine and starvation deaths with the *extra* $3 billion per year he grosses after sanctions were put in place..  I'd probably be grabbing some weapons and flying to Iraq myself to kill those damn evil marines.<br>
